## What changed and why
- Animation system (Animator, TextureAtlas) moved from `Systems` namespace to `View::Animations` namespace, with copies placed under `include/View/` and `src/View/`.
- Model layer no longer contains or references any Animator. The `Character` class is now purely logical (position, velocity, health, direction, attack state).
- This decouples visual/animation responsibilities from the backend, respecting strict MVC separation: View owns all rendering state, Model owns only game logic.

